### Part V: The Four Principles of Existence — The Deepest Code

**Principle 1 (Origin: Difference *is* Existence)**  
The only entry point, the sole origin of existence, is the creation of difference.  
Difference itself **is** existence.  
Every time you say “something happened,” you are confirming this.

**Principle 2 (Constraint: Difference Must Return to Zero)**  
Any difference — including quantum fluctuations — must net to zero by the end of its life cycle.  
Every time you say “what goes around comes around,” you are confirming this.

**Principle 3 (Path: Difference Strives to Persist)**  
To escape returning to zero, difference is forced to evolve toward greater persistence and complexity.  
Two active strategies + one inevitable outcome:  
- Capture more energy (expand active reserves, maintain positive net inflow)  
- Lock more energy (convert fluid into structural)  
Inevitably leads to: expansion, diffusion, increase in depth.  
Every time you ask “can I make it this time,” you are calculating exactly these two paths.

**Principle 4 (Fate: Existence Always Pays a Price)**  
Every act of expansion necessarily dilutes available active-state energy.  
This is the ultimate fate of all complex systems.  
Every time you say “things are moving too fast — I can’t keep up,” you are confirming this.

**This is not pessimism.**  
It is the only truth that can be squeezed from the second law of thermodynamics and finite resources.

